{
  "id": "medium_02_ts",
  "title": "Request Logger (TS)",
  "difficulty": "medium",
  "category": "Class vs instance variable",
  "description": "Given a list of service entries, each containing a service name and a list of request IDs, return a dict mapping each service name to **only its own** request IDs.\n\nEach input entry: `{\"service\": str, \"ids\": [str, ...]}`\n\n**Example 1:**\nInput:\n```\n[\n  {\"service\": \"api\",   \"ids\": [\"req_1\", \"req_2\"]},\n  {\"service\": \"db\",    \"ids\": [\"req_3\"]},\n  {\"service\": \"cache\", \"ids\": [\"req_4\", \"req_5\"]}\n]\n```\nOutput:\n```\n{\"api\": [\"req_1\", \"req_2\"], \"db\": [\"req_3\"], \"cache\": [\"req_4\", \"req_5\"]}\n```\n\n**Constraints:**\n- `1 <= len(service_requests) <= 50`\n- Each service name is unique in the input.\n- `1 <= len(ids) <= 20` per entry.\n\n**Note:** A new `RequestLog` instance is created for each service — yet request IDs from earlier services keep appearing. Where exactly is `log` defined, and is it truly per-instance?",
  "files": [
    {
      "name": "main.ts",
      "editable": true
    },
    {
      "name": "logger.ts",
      "editable": true
    }
  ],
  "entry_module": "main",
  "entry_function": "collectLogs",
  "test_cases": [
    {
      "args": [
        [
          {
            "service": "api",
            "ids": [
              "req_1",
              "req_2"
            ]
          },
          {
            "service": "db",
            "ids": [
              "req_3"
            ]
          },
          {
            "service": "cache",
            "ids": [
              "req_4",
              "req_5"
            ]
          }
        ]
      ],
      "expected": {
        "api": [
          "req_1",
          "req_2"
        ],
        "db": [
          "req_3"
        ],
        "cache": [
          "req_4",
          "req_5"
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
  "hint": "Is `log` defined on the instance (in the constructor), or somewhere else? What happens when multiple instances push to the same array reference?",
  "requirements_updates": [
    {
      "id": "upd_1",
      "trigger": {
        "type": "random",
        "min_runs": 2,
        "max_runs": 4
